                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " model. The aperture- coding patterns were set to the corresponding parameters in the learned AcqNet model. Figure 7 shows the coding patterns and experimental setup (left), an image frame and event stacks obtained from the camera (center), and the light field reconstructed from them (right). Our method performed well with real 3- D scenes; the parallax information was successfully embedded into the events, and a light field was reconstructed with visually convincing quality. Please refer to the supplementary video for more results with better visualization."
